credit_line: Bequest of Mrs. John Innes Kane
title: Cellarette
description: Upright, rectangular form; veneered surface with two drawers surmounted by a drop front panel with inlay of light wood bands around edges, stars at corners and gilt bronze escutcheon in form of trophy; drawers with gilt bronze circular pulls and palmette-form escutchions; rectangular gilt bronze handles on left and right side; two paw feet with gilt foliate decoration in front; turned rear feet.
name: Cellarette
